            <div class="text">
				   <h2>What is FrozenFlower?</h2>
				   <p>FrozenFlower is a Photoblog aggregator. All content is taken from several photoblogs with the authorization of their owners. FrozenFlower mission is:</p>
					<ul>
					  <li>To be a place where anyone can enjoy good photos</li>
					  <li>Help photographers make their work known</li>
					  <li>To be a community the photographers</li>
					  <li>Generate traffic to the photoblogs of its members</li>
					  <li>Have fun! :)</li>
					</ul>
				   <h2>Who is behind FrozenFlower?</h2>
				   <p><a href="http://www.simplice.net/en">Nuno Barreto</a>, a portuguese web developer and a photography amateur. My photoblog is <a href="http://fotosnatureza.blogs.sapo.pt">Fotos da Natureza</a>.</p>
				   <h2>Why create FrozenFlower?</h2>
				   <p>I searched for a service like this for Photoblogs, and found none. So, I decided to create one myself. Some of the inspiration comes from <a href="http://www.planetgeek.org">PlanetGeek</a></p>
				   <h2>Who can join FrozenFlower?</h2>
				   <p>Anyone that follows the rules, and that is approved by the members of FrozenFlower. The rules are:</p>
					<ul>
					  <li>Have a photoblog with a RSS/Atom Feed</li>
					  <li>Photos in the feed must be at least 500px wide or tall</li>
					  <li>Photos must be yours</li>
					  <li>No pornography (nudity is allowed, within common sense)</li>
					  <li>No photos that go against human rights, or that condone discrimination or violence</li>
					  <li>Any other rule that we fancy in the future</li>
					</ul>
				   <h2>How do I join FrozenFlower?</h2>
					<p>Any request should be sent to us in <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/frozenflower">Google Groups</a> (press <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/frozenflower/post?sendowner=1">contact the owner</a>), and it will be submited for approval by the members in the mailing list. If a suficient number of members aproves it, the person will then be invited to join, and will become a full blood member.</p>
				   <h2>What is de advantage of having a photoblog in FrozenFlower?</h2>
				   <p>Having a photoblog in a aggregator like FrozenFlower has several advantages:</p>
					<ul>
					  <li>It will give more visibility to your work</li>
					  <li>It will generate traffic to your photoblog</li>
					  <li>You will be part of a community where you can learn together</li>
					</ul>
				   <h2>Why the ads?</h2>
				   <p>I want to be able to pay the web hosting service. Probably I will not profit much from this project, but I hope it will be enough to pay the costs.</p>
				   <h2>Why the name FrozenFlower?</h2>
				   <p>My wife likes it, and I do too :). It's not easy to find a good domain in our days, and we tried playing with the word frozen (because a photo freezes something), and after many tries, we liked the sound of FrozenFlower.</p>
				   <h2>What is the technology behind FrozenFlower?</h2>
				   <p>The script that aggregates the feeds and puts them in the <a href="http://www.mysql.com">mySQL</a> database is made in <a href="http://www.python.org">Python</a>, with the help of <a href="http://www.feedparser.org">feedparser</a>. The website is done in <a href="http://www.php.net">PHP</a> and <a href="http://www.smarty.net">Smarty</a>.</p>
				   <h2>Where is my post?</h2>
				   <p>If your post doesn't show up, it can be for a number of technical reasons, in which case you should report the problem in the mailing list. But it can also be because the post has no photo.</p>
